“Hi Y/N.” He puts his phone in his lap and picks at his nails.

“Hi. Uh, do you know where Phil’s at?” I turn to face him, my cheek on my fist.

“No I don’t. He just said he was going out with Willow.” He shrugs and glances up.

“Again? Damn.” I turn to face the Tv. A movie with Jennifer Lawrence was playing. Red sparrow to be exact. Dan stared at the tv, seeming extremely concentrated on what was going on. His hand between his thighs whilst the other one behind his head. He looked good, even if he was in some pyjamas. And he knew he looked good, he knew I knew he looked good and he would make it almost painful to keep my hands off of him. The fact that when Dan and I used to date, I would constantly call him hot or beautiful or adorable didn’t help my case whatsoever.

“So, you and Phil are together?” Dan lazily looks at me with slight hooded eyes.

“I don’t really know. He says he’s too busy for a relationship.” I look down at the carpet, feeling sudden guilt.

“Hmm, sucks.” Dan smirks a bit.

“What? Is that amusing to you?” I bitterly laugh.

“Kind of.” He chuckles. “Only because he seemed to care about you in the beginning and just leaves you. Kind of like what I did yeah?” He puts his hand on my cheek. “Doesn’t It make you feel like he just used you? For sex? For his own fulfilling desires? Cause you were so desperate for attention, you just got the same thing. Except I actually cared about you and wasn’t cheating on you with some bitch. But you, oh you darling we’re just too needy weren’t you?”

He sits closer and pulls me closer onto him. My leg on his lap as he runs his hand up and down it. “Don’t you want to make him feel like shit too? I mean, he makes you feel like you’re nothing. Isn’t that how I made you feel? Like I didn’t love you. So you had to go find someone else who would act as if they cared about you.”

“But I don’t want anyone to feel bad.” I whisper.

“Yeah you do! You made me feel bad! You made yourself feel bad! Why not make the person hurting you feel hurt? Cause all of a sudden you’re a good person? You’d be lying to yourself.” He holds my hands.

“Why would Phil even care? We aren’t dating.” I sit up straight.

“I suppose.” He shrugs and lies back on the couch, pulling me on top of him. “Just don’t even think about it anymore. Tell me everything you want to feel and I’ll make it happen.”

—

And with that it happened. Phil still wasn’t home even after the whole thing. Dan was comforting me, whispering sweet nothings in my ear as he played with my hair. It was weird how he wasn’t leaving me. He didn’t seem busy.

“How do you feel?” He looks over at me with a sweet expression.

“You make me feel good.” I close my eyes.

“I know. You wouldn’t have been begging for more if I didn’t.” He smirks. I laugh at the amount of cockiness he had.

“Dan! Y/N!”

“Oh shit.” I whisper yell. I sit up but Dan pushes me back down.

“No! Let him find us. In such a wonderful state.” Dan chuckles. “Maybe he’ll be jealous. That I got to lick you clean, feel your walls tighten around me, telling me you want to taste me on your tongue. God fucking dammit, I’ve missed the feeling of you so much. The way you moan, the way you tell me to go faster, harder. And your sweet, tight pussy.” He sounded aggravated, as if he really did miss me. Phil’s footsteps got closer but I just ignored them and laughed at the shitty jokes Dan was making.

“What the fuck?” I hear Phil laugh.

“Hi Phil, how was Willow?” I sit up.

“She was fine, what the hell is this though?” Phil drops the bag on the floor.

“What are you about to do? Join us? You wanna suck my dick?” Dan squints his eyes.

“I’d rather not.” Phil rolls his eyes. “So you’ve moved on quite quickly.”

“Moved on from what? Our friends with benefits relationship?” I tilt my head.

“Is that what it was?” Phil responds laughing and crossing his arms.

“It’s what you made it.” I pick up my shirt from the left side of Dan’s bed. “Besides, you seem to be losing interest in me.”

“And? What did dan just suddenly like you?”

“I suppose.”

“Well, how can I make it better?”

As soon as he asked that question, a smirk pulls on my lips.

“Come here.” I point. He slowly walks and sits on the bed.

“Show me what you’re good for.”
